fields.title: Saigon Ground Cassia Cinnamon
fields.description: Spicy and sweet, this cinnamon is our most popular varietal. Its high volatile oil content makes the bark extremely potent. Vietnamese cinnamon is fiery, rich, fragrant, and amazing with chocolate or in cinnamon rolls, where it can be the entire flavor.

fields.title: Back of the Yards Garlic Pepper Butcher's Rub
fields.description: If one flavor combination could represent The Spice House, it is this hard-working butcher's rub. Back of the Yards, our most popular blend, is ideal for grilling, great in burgers, and perfect with fish or eggs. It takes inspiration from the many immigrant cooking traditions that grew out of Chicago's historic meatpacking district.

fields.title: Lake Shore Drive Shallot & Herb Seasoning
fields.description: Inspired by the glorious green foliage along the shores of Lake Michigan, our Lake Shore Drive Shallot & Herb Seasoning includes chives, scallions, green peppercorns, and shallots. It adds an elegant but bold finish to fish, omelettes, and vegetable.

fields.title: Gateway to the North Maple Garlic Seasoning
fields.description: One of our most popular blends, this seasoning is sweet, savory, and made with real Wisconsin maple sugar. Named after the maple industry hub of Marinette County, Gateway to the North compliments pork, baked beans, and sweet potatoes.

fields.title: Vulcan's Fire Salt
fields.description: This fiery salt is named for Vulcan, the Roman god of fire. Vulcan Fire Salt owes its spicy, deep flavor to a secret ingredient discovered by The Spice House's founder many decades ago. Sprinkle it on popcorn, garlic bread, or scrambled eggs.

fields.title: Brisket of Love Barbecue Rub
fields.description:
A Spice House manager created this sumptuous blend as a parting gift for guests at his barbecue-inspired wedding. It is sweet and tangy with a peppery bite, perfect for slow-smoked brisket. Use this blend to add some kick to your Shabbat dinner, corned beef, or homemade pastrami.
Oh!

fields.title: Best Sellers Collection
fields.description: Among cooks, the seasonings in the Best Sellers Collection are our most popular. Whether you're baking salmon for a weeknight supper, making steak for a Sunday roast, or mixing bloody marys for a summer brunch, these rubs, salts, and seasonings will turn any dish into a crowdpleaser. Although we could never pick a favorite, we are delighted you have.

fields.title: Medium Chili Powder
fields.description: Hailing from the American Southwest, chili powder is at the core of Tex-Mex cooking. Use it to season meat for chili, tacos, and enchilada sauce. Our powder is mixed in small batches.

fields.title: Back of the Yards Collection
fields.description: Here in the Windy City, you can tour dishes from around the globe just by neighborhood-hopping. This collection of rubs and seasonings celebrates locals whose families hail from Southeast Asia, Latin America, and Eastern Europe. Bring the world's tables together at yours by adding any of these blends to a new or favorite recipe.

fields.title: Smoked Spanish Hot Paprika, Pimenton de la Vera Picante
fields.description: Made from peppers slowly dried over an oak fire, this smoky paprika forms the flavor base for chorizo and patatas bravas. It also pairs well with grilled chicken.

fields.title: Lake Shore Drive Collection
fields.description: The blends in this collection are divined from dishes served at Greektown tavernas, Bronzeville barbeques, and at family dinners on Lake Shore Drive. These Chicago-essential spices and seasonings will help you celebrate a culinary heritage that is just one of the many wonderful reasons we know the Second City really comes in first.

fields.title: Turkish Bay Leaves
fields.description: The Oracle of Delphi chewed fresh laurel leaves for divine inspiration. When dried, they make for inspired sauces, stews, soups, and curries. We chased the bay leaf around the world and decided the large, fragrant Turkish variety is our favorite.

fields.title: Black Tea Tropical Colada
fields.description:
Black Tea cocktail styled with a very creamy and tropical flavor, with coconut and pineapple. 
A mix with an intense flavor that transports us to tropical climates. The black tea base gives character to the sweetness of pineapple and coconut. In our online recipe book you can find an original preparation developed by Tea Shop that reminds us of the famous Piña Colada cocktail.

fields.title: Red Tea (Pu Erh) Choco Turrón
fields.description:
The sweet tradition of the holidays in a crunchy and sweet-toothed Pu Erh Red Tea blend that melts in your mouth.
An irresistible and cheerful combination of chocolate and puffed rice, enriched with delicious Pu Erh Red Tea. A tea to enjoy at breakfast and snacks, alone, with milk or vegetable drink. Besides being a whim, it is a delicious way to hydrate yourself during the day.

fields.title: White Tea Snow Christmas
fields.description:
The expression "beauty" of Christmas, sweet and creamy taste for a festive and welcoming winter. 
The expression "beauty" of Christmas of sweet and creamy taste that evokes the classic caramelised baked apple tart. Ideal to enjoy in a festive and cosy winter. Its delicate and sweet aroma is an invitation to the well-being that cradles the magnificent properties of White Tea, considered the beauty tea par excellence. It provides antioxidants, is purifying and diuretic.

fields.title: Black Tea Black Mountain Fruit
fields.description:
Sweet and fruity black tea for beginners in the world of tea, with an invigorating and energising blend of black tea and blackberry, with a sweet and slightly astringent flavour. 
Natural antioxidant and moderately tannic from our range of energising teas.  Black Tea is the leaves of Camellia Sinensis with complete oxidation, giving them intensity in tannins and theine.

fields.title: Ceylon Spicy Black Tea
fields.description:
Wild black tea from Adam's Peak, Sri Lanka, with the spicy flavor of cloves and cardamom. The large, dark leaves give this beverage an enveloping and lingering aroma. 
FOREST FRIENDLY TEA is an eco-sustainable project born in harmony with nature and the power of the earth. The FOREST FRIENDLY range is composed of wild, free-range, indigenous and sustainable teas from the mountain forests of Northern Thailand and Adam's Peak in Sri Lanka.

fields.title: Green Tea Asian Wellness
fields.description:
Superfood blend of green tea, tropical fruits, spirulina and aloe vera with a fresh and juicy taste.
Mixed with superfood ingredients. Moringa is a superfood plant rich in vitamins A, B and C, proteins and minerals such as potassium, calcium, iron and magnesium. 
Its slightly bitter taste balances the sweet taste of Green Tea and mango. Due to its attractive taste and its versatility, it can be consumed cold or hot, it becomes an essential drink in the pantry. Green Tea is an antioxidant and diuretic.

fields.title: Green Tea Organic Vietnam Lao Cai Green Op
fields.description:
Organic Green Tea from northern Vietnam with silvery shoots and whole, young leaves, harvested from wild trees.
In Vietnam, it is common for tea trees to feed on biodiversity, without the need for an irrigation system or pesticides. In addition, the garden of origin is certified "Fairtrade" and is harvested manually by the Tay Ethinic, native to the furthest village in the province of Lao Cai (next to China).

fields.title: Green Tea Matcha Gracia Blend Green
fields.description:
Iconic, classic, floral and Mediterranean character blend, inspired by the origins of Tea Shop. 
An ideal mixture to start in the world of tea. Matcha Gracia Blend Green with its flavor catches any palate and makes you fly to the origins of Tea Shop. The umami flavor of Matcha and the fresh flavor of green tea are balanced by the enveloping sweetness of vanilla and flowers.

fields.title: Red Tea (Pu Erh) Praliné
fields.description:
Authentic praline with Pu Erh, carob, apple, hazelnut, cinnamon, chicory and flowers. 
Delicious Pu Erh Red Tea, similar to the famous specialty "praliné" originating in the French city of Montardis, which helps cleanse the body while sweetening the palate with its tasty and digestive mix of flavors. Antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, stimulating and helps improve digestion.

fields.title: Green Tea Magic Mango
fields.description:
An explosion of flavor with Green Tea, mango and the Superfood moringa. 
Moringa is a Superfood plant rich in vitamins A, B and C, protein and minerals such as potassium, calcium, iron and magnesium. Its slightly bitter taste balances the sweetness of green tea and mango. Thanks to its attractive taste and its versatility, it can be consumed hot and cold, making it an essential drink in the pantry. Mixture with strong antioxidant power thanks to Green Tea and a source of vitamins and minerals thanks to moringa, mango and apple.

fields.title: Black Tea Berry Fields
fields.description:
Mixture of Black Tea with wild fruit and beet, ideal for breakfast and snacks.
Its sweet and enveloping aroma offers versatility in hot or cold consumption, only, with milk or vegetable drink. A perfect base to prepare delicious and nutritious Smoothies. Black Tea is a natural mild stimulant, which helps to clear the mind and relax the muscles. Red fruits along with beets are a source of vitamins and antioxidants.

fields.title: Black Tea Earl Grey Crème
fields.description:
The creamiest black Earl Grey tea with bergamot and sweet notes, a suggestive alternative to lovers of our classic Earl Grey. 
A creamy tea, with a lot of personality, which is enhanced by adding milk. Earl Grey remains one of the most famous and consumed mixes in the world.

fields.title: The Last Dab | APOLLO
fields.description: The Last Dab: Apollo joins the Hot Ones lineup as the new king of Mt. Scoville, hero of hot sauces, and crusher of celebrities and chiliheads alike. The Apollo Pepper has been carefully bred and nurtured by Guinness World Record holding chili breeder Smokin’ Ed Currie of Puckerbutt Pepper Co from prized strains of his famed Carolina Reaper and Pepper X. The Apollo brings this heritage to new heights of capsaicin, packing a more concentrated punch than any of its forebears. The flavor of The Apollo comes from the sweetness of Carolina Reaper, tinged with the earthiness of Pepper X - it’s a culinary powerhouse. The heat profile of The Apollo Pepper is akin to having your head slowly lit aflame. You feel the fire consume your entire skull, your tongue smolders, burning tears pour from your eyes. And then, five minutes later, the ride is over, your heart rate returns to normal, the panic subsides. This pepper is like no other.

fields.title: Karma | Scorpion Disco
fields.description: Gene from Karma Sauce Co is bringing the boogie with this scorching hot Scorpion pepper hot sauce. One of the hottest on earth, Trinidad Scorpion peppers lend this sauce their signature floral flavor and sharp heat before being backed up by ghost peppers, chocolate habaneros and 7 Pot Primo peppers. These chiles are going full Saturday Night Fever, and your taste buds are their dance floor! Excellent on fried chicken dishes (think the world’s best hot cherry sauce), jerk marinades or mixed into a rich yogurt for a flaming hot dipping sauce.

fields.title: Hotter Than El | Love Burns
fields.description: Following their ghost hot sauce’s debut on Hot Ones Season 12, Hotter Than El is back with a spicier spot in the lineup at #7. This bright, vinegar-forward sauce gets its pleasant peppery notes from a mix of 7 Pot Primo, Carolina Reaper and Trinidad Scorpion peppers. Plus some ghost chile powder for good measure! Lime juice and carrots add freshness and tang, making this an excellent hot wing sauce (mix with melted butter unless you’re ready to handle the burn).

fields.title: High Desert | Tikk-Hot Masala
fields.description: An aromatic spice blend, this hot sauce brings creamy coconut milk and tangy tomatoes blended with a medium-hot mix of Anaheim, ghost and Carolina Reaper peppers - basically all the flavors of your favorite Tikka Masala. A little agave nectar adds sweetness, with fresh garlic and toasted cumin bringing the savory. A newcomer to the Hot Ones hot sauce family, this medium-hot sauce turns up the volume of curries and soups, as well as hearty meats like lamb.

fields.title: Ginger Goat | The Original Goat (The OG)
fields.description: Ginger hot sauce! Need we say more? Ginger Goat lives up to its name with a billy goat kick of zippy, throat-clearing ginger root that is perfectly balanced with bright, tropical smoked pineapple. Slow building heat from just a handful of Carolina Reapers in each batch add a tingle at the back of the throat. If ginger health shots were a delicious sauce, they’d taste like this. Marinade chicken, toss it on salad, top healthy grain bowls and more - the possibilities are endless with this one!

fields.title: Hot Ones | Los Calientes Barbacoa
fields.description: Inspired by one of our favorite culinary traditions, Los Calientes Barbacoa pays homage to the origins of barbecue. Deep earthy notes from chipotle peppers blend with applewood smoked red jalapenos to evoke the essential elements of ancient barbecue: earth, smoke and heat. Sweet apricots and tart tomatillos balance things out and compliment the bright citrus notes, while culantro and cumin add herby complexity. Medium-heat habanero heat spreads warmly over the tongue. No one ingredient outshines the others, for a sauce that is uniquely complete - just like the satisfaction of that perfect bite. A new must-have for all your summer favorites: slow cooking meats, grilling veggies, topping tacos and so much more!

fields.title: Cantina Royal | Tomasa
fields.description: For those familiar with Catina Royal’s Tamaulipeka hot sauce from Hot Ones Season 11, Tomasa is similarly rich but has a darker hue that hints at its intense flavor. The sauce gets its inky color from earthy roasted manzano chiles, which are highlighted by a strong hit of garlic (super strong!) and the sauce’s silky corn oil base. Smokey and savory, Tomasa brings out the umami in everything from tacos to pizza to dumplings.

fields.title: Savir Foods | Jala Pepa
fields.description: Savir Foods chef Josue Rivas focuses on fresh, veggie-forward food, and this hot sauce is no exception. Jala Pepa was inspired by his favorite herby Peruvian dish. A new must-have for cilantro lovers, the grassy notes blend with jalapenos and golden aji amarillo peppers. The addition of grape seed oil and dates create a creamy texture that, combined with the easy heat level, make it tempting to use on all occasions. Try on your next burrito bowl, avocado toast, or swirl into hummus!

fields.title: Hot Ones | The Classic
fields.description: The #1 sauce on Hot Ones! When it came time to craft the perfect kick-off to Sean's spicy conversations, we knew we wanted a hot sauce that was as timeless as the chicken wing. After sampling many of the world's best peppers we decided to go with Chile de Arbol, prized for its complex, fresh flavors. The chiles and sauce are grown/made by our great friend Smokin' Ed Currie of Puckerbutt Pepper Co, who says it may be the tastiest hot sauce he's ever crafted. For lots of flavor and a healthy tang, try it on everything, and use liberally.

fields.title: Season 15 Hot Ones Trio
fields.description: The signature Hot Ones hot sauces anchoring the Season 15 lineup! This pack features the mildest, mid-range and hottest sauces on the wings of doom. Hot Ones’ uber versatile #1 sauce, The Classic, is an updated take on American hot sauce traditions that have only gotten better with experience. Next is medium heat from the newest addition to the Hot Ones hot sauce fam, Los Calientes Barbacoa, which pays homage to the ancient roots of barbecue with smoky chipotles and habaneros. Finishing things off is The Last Dab: Apollo, the hottest sauce to grace the 10th wing in the lineup. The only sauce in the world made with Smokin’ Ed’s newest proprietary pepper, The Apollo will leave you gasping for air. Careful around the eyes!

fields.title: Season 15 Heat Pack
fields.description: The wilder side of Hot Ones Season 15! These medium to blazing hot sauces spice up the 6, 7 and 9th spots in the lineup. High Desert Sauce Co’s Tikk-Hot Masala starts heating things up with a modest mix of ghost pepper and Carolina Reaper. Bold garam masala spices and coconut milk base balance the heat of those pepper power players. In the #7 spot, Hotter Than El’s Love Burns ups the ante even further with a blend of 7 Pot Primos, Reapers and Scorpion peppers. Karma Sauce came through with a scorcher of a #9 sauce, Scorpion Disco. Four different super hot peppers combine to put the fever in Saturday night. The pack for pepperheads and anyone looking for a challenge!

fields.title: Season 15 Warmup Pack
fields.description: The not-so-wild sauces from the Hot Ones lineup! The first half of the Season 15 lineup features sauces with destination-inspired ingredients and incredible depth of flavor. Take #2 sauce Jala Pepa, which features cilantro and the aji amarillo, inspired by the flavors of Peru. In the #3 spot, Cantina Royal’s Tomasa channels the flavors of Mexico with a luxurious oil base and earthy charred manzano peppers. At #5, The Original Goat is made in Canada but tastes straight out of the tropics thanks to smoked pineapple and a heaping dose of fresh ginger. All three have just-right heat, perfect for folks focused on flavor and don’t want to break a sweat.

fields.title: Red Bull Energy Drink, 8.4 Fl Oz (12 pack)
fields.description:
RED BULL GIVES YOU WINGS
Inspired by functional drinks from the Far East, Dietrich Mateschitz founded Red Bull in the mid-1980s. He developed a new product and a unique marketing concept and launched Red Bull Energy Drink on April 1, 1987 in Austria. A brand new product category - Energy Drinks - was born.

fields.title: Hawaiian Punch Fruit Juicy Red, 1 Gallon
fields.description: Enjoy the refreshing taste of Hawaiian Punch Fruit Juicy Red. When it comes to fruit juice drinks, Hawaiian Punch is The Big Kahuna. Bursting with the bold taste of natural fruit juices, Hawaiian Punch fruit juice is a delicious and unique taste that kids and the entire family will enjoy. This family-sized 1-gal container is the ideal drink for dinner time or anytime. Hawaiian Punch fruit punch is both caffeine and carbonation-free and provides 100 percent of the daily value of vitamin C. Treat your family to the delicious taste of Hawaiian Punch. The large bottle is ideal sharing with family and friends.

fields.title: Keystone All Natural Pork, 28 oz Can
fields.description: Create a delicious meal with this Keystone Heat & Serve Pork Nutrition. It is fully cooked and made with all-natural ingredients. This Keystone canned meat comes in a 28 oz size. This product is minimally processed and contains no artificial ingredients.

fields.title: Banza Cavatappi Pasta, 8 oz
fields.description: Chickpeas make delicious pasta. That's why we used them to create Banza. Now it's your turn. So bake your ziti, mac your cheese, and pesto the rest-o, because your favorite family meal is back on the menu!

fields.title: Payday, Chocolatey Covered Peanut Caramel Standard Candy Bars, 24 pack
fields.description: PAYDAY Peanut Caramel Bars have been a favorite of peanut fans for decades and now they have a chocolatey coating!. Treat yourself to a delicious treat made from salty peanuts and a chewy caramel filling. Each bar is individually wrapped for snacking on the go or sharing with friends. This candy is OU Certified as a Kosher food. This product ships as 1.85-ounce bars in a pack of 24.

fields.description: 1.1 ounces (or 31 grams, if you will) of the most delicious cotton candy lollipops you will ever taste. its like standing in line at the local fair and getting handed sweet deliciousness on a stick that you then devour within 2.5 minutes while sharing none with your pesky little brother! except you dont have to stand in line for this cotton candy lollipop! it lasts an hour and is small enough to hide from that pesky little brother, so you still dont have to share! original gourmets patented gravity-pouring process (yes, it turns out you can patent things like that) ensures every sucker lives up to its gourmet name.

fields.title: Arm & Hammer Pure Baking Soda, 12 lb
fields.description: Discover the secret of ARM & HAMMER Baking Soda, the simple solution for a clean and fresh home. Baking soda is the most versatile product in your home and ARM & HAMMER is the most recognized brand. You know that Baking soda is great for cooking and baking. Now, discover more than 100 ways to save time and money with Baking Soda, from cleaning your carpets to getting rid of pet odors, making laundry sparkle, creating inexpensive craft for kids, and even enjoying a spa-worthy pedicure. Whether you need a quick solution for mopping dirty kitchen floors, a non-abrasive way to scrub bathroom countertops, or a chemical-free way to clean toys, furniture, pots and pans, we've got tips to make every room in your home shine and smell fresh. Put ARM & HAMMER to work all around your home! With its natural pure and gentle cleaning power, there isn't a place in your home where dirt and odors are safe.

fields.description: Est 1924. Authentic. We've always made our honey one way: Locally. We partner with American beekeepers from coast to coast to bring you authentic wildflower honey that stays true to the blooming flowers our bees chose. It's raw & unfiltered, straight from American beekeepers to you. Bee happy. US Grade A strained. localhivehoney.com Facebook (at)localhivehoney. Support the American Beekeeper.
